            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Hi! @Delerme sorry for the tag üôè this has been open for a while, so I'm afraid you won't get a notification.\n\nI've landed here after doing some researching due to an unbelievably slow `eslint` LSP performance.\n\nHere's my experience: I'm on insert mode typing, and as soon as I go into normal mode I can literally see how eslint goes character by character I've typed, linting everything as an error until it (after a few seconds, or even minutes) catches up with my changes.\n\nThis is an almost unbearable experience üò£\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/769d0809-fdbd-4d70-9f7c-8b320c72833d\n\nThis is my `eslint` configuration:\n\n```lua\nreturn {\n    settings = {\n        format = false,\n    },\n    flags = {\n        allow_incremental_sync = false,\n        debounce_text_changes = 1000,\n    },\n}\n```\n\nThis doesn't even seem to have any sort of effect üò≠ (I'm on `NVIM v0.11.4` btw). I'm trying to follow up on the conversation here or in https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/30055, but honestly it's very hard to understand what's the solution for this, if there's any ü´§\n\nHelp üôèüòî",
